AndRangeFeature - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.features
Tests all tokens within a certain range for a certain criterion, and returns true only if all of them satisfy the criterion.
Start and end are absolute indexes.
If either refer to a postion outside of the token sequence, will test all valid tokens only.
If no tokens are tested, will return null.
If any test returns null, will return null.

com.joliciel.talismane.posTagger - package com.joliciel.talismane.posTagger
Package enabling the part-of-speech tagging of a TokenSequence.
The central class is the (PosTagger).
It tags based on a previously constructed classificaton model, converting the model's outcomes to PosTag using the currently set PosTagSet.
The PosTagSet is set via TalismaneSession.setPosTagSet(PosTagSet).
The pos-tagger prodces a PosTagSequence which is a list of PosTaggedToken.
It can be evaluated via a PosTaggerEvaluator.

CorpusModifier - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.extensions.corpus
Modifies a corpus in simple ways, by replacing labels with other ones, or removing dependencies.
The input file has the following format:
GOVPOS\tGOV\tDEPPOS\tDEP\tLABEL\tACTION\tNEWLABEL
Where GOVPOS is the governor's pos-tag, or * for any.
GOV is the governor's word form, or * for any.
DEPPOS is the dependent's pos-tag, or * for any
DEP is the dependent's word form, or * for any
LABEL is the current label, or * for any
ACTION is either Replace or Remove
NEWLABEL is a new label, only required if action is Replace.
Any line starting with # is ignored.
CorpusModifier(ParseConfigurationProcessor, List<String>) - Constructor for class com.joliciel.talismane.extensions.corpus.CorpusModifier
 
CorpusProjectifier - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.extensions.corpus
Transforms a non-projective corpus to a projective corpus by attaching non-projective arcs to the nearest projective head.
CorpusProjectifier(ParseConfigurationProcessor) - Constructor for class com.joliciel.talismane.extensions.corpus.CorpusProjectifier

getTransitionBasedGlobalLearningParser(FeatureWeightVector, ParsingConstrainer, Set<ParseConfigurationFeature<?>>, int) - Method in interface com.joliciel.talismane.parser.ParserService
A non-deterministic parser implementing transition based parsing, using a Shift-Reduce algorithm, but applying global learning.
The features are thus used to rank parse configurations after all valid transitions have been applied, rather than being used to select the next transition for an existing configuration.

HistorySearchFeature - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.posTagger.features
Returns the first token in a given range which matches a certain criterion, or null if no such token is found.
If a start index is provided as a second argument, will start looking at this index, otherwise at the current token's index-1.
If an end index is provided as a third argument, will continue until the end index, otherwise until token 0.
All indexes must be <= the current history size, otherwise only valid indexes will be looked at.
If start index >= end index, will look backwards, otherwise will look forwards.

Useful for ensuring that inner-pattern decisions are always respected (unless two patterns overlap in the same sequence), thus ensuring that multi-token compound words are either made compound as a whole, or not at all.

NextLetterCapitalFeature - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.sentenceDetector.features
In the following descriptions, the current boundary is surrounded by square brackets.
Returns "CapitalAfterInitial" for any pattern like: W[.] Shakespeare
Returns "CapitalAfterQuote" for any pattern like: blah di blah[.]" Hello or blah di blah[.] "Hello
Returns "CapitalAfterDash" for any pattern like: blah di blah[.] - Hello
Returns "true" for any other pattern like: "blah di blah[.] Hello
Returns "false" otherwise.
Note that there MUST be whitespace between the separator and the capital letter for it to be considered a capital letter.
NextLetterCapitalFeature() - Constructor for class com.joliciel.talismane.sentenceDetector.features.NextLetterCapitalFeature

OrRangeFeature - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.features
Tests all tokens within a certain range for a certain criterion, and returns true if any one of them satisfies the criterion.
Start and end are absolute indexes.
If either refer to a postion outside of the token sequence, will test all valid tokens only.
If no tokens are tested, will return null.
If any test returns null, will return null.

ParserRule - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.parser.features
A ParserRule is specified by a boolean feature and a Transition.
If the boolean feature evaluates to true, the configuration will automatically be assigned the Transition in question, without taking any further decisions.
Negative rules are also possible: in this case, the Transition in question is eliminated from the set of possible Transitions (unless no other Transitions are possible).

PosTaggerRule - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.posTagger.features
A PosTaggerRule is specified by a boolean feature and a PosTag.
If the boolean feature evaluates to true, the token will automatically be assigned the PosTag in question, without taking any further decisions.
Negative rules are also possible: in this case, the PosTag in question is eliminated from the set of possible PosTags (unless no other PosTags are possible).

A corpus reader that expects one pos-tagged token per line, and analyses the line content based on a regex supplied during construction.
The regex needs to contain the following two capturing groups, indicated by the following strings:
%TOKEN%: the token - note that we assume CoNLL formatting (with underscores for spaces and for empty tokens).

SurroundingsFeature - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.sentenceDetector.features
Examines the atomic tokens from n before the boundary to n after the boundary.
For each token, if it is whitespace, adds " " to the result.
If it is a separator, adds the original separator to the result.
If it is a capitalised word, adds, "W", "Wo" or "Word", depending on whether the word is 1 letter, 2 letters, or more.
Otherwise adds "word" to the result.

Talismane - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane
An interface for processing a Reader from TalismaneConfig.getReader() and writing the analysis result to a Writer from TalismaneConfig.getWriter().
Not thread-safe: a single Talismane cannot be used by multiple threads simultaneously.
The output format is determined by the processor corresponding to TalismaneConfig.getEndModule().
This is accomplished by calling #runCommand(TalismaneConfig), and passing it all the configuration options.

TalismaneConfig - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane
An abstract base class for loading, storing and translating configuration information to be passed to Talismane when processing.
Implementing classes must include language-specific implementation resources.
The processing must go from a given start module to a given end module in sequence, where the modules available are: Sentence detector, Tokeniser, Pos tagger, Parser.
There is a default input format for each start module, which can be over-ridden by providing a regex for processing lines of input.

TextFileMultivaluedResource - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.machineLearning
An external resource read from a text file.
The default name will be the filename.
If a line starts with the string "Name: ", the default name will be replaced by this name.
If a line starts with the string "Multivalued: false", an exception gets thrown.
All lines starting with # are skipped.
Any other line will be broken up by tabs:
For multi-valued resources, the second-to-last tab is the class, the last tab is the weight.
All previous tabs are considered to be key components.
The same set of key components can have multiple classes with different weights.
TextFileMultivaluedResource(File) - Constructor for class com.joliciel.talismane.machineLearning.TextFileMultivaluedResource

If a line starts with the string "Name: ", the default name will be replaced by this name.
If a line starts with the string "Multivalued: true", an exception gets thrown.
All lines starting with # are skipped.
Any other line will be broken up by tabs:
One tab per key component, and the last tab is the class.

The default name will be the filename.

TokeniserPatternManager - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.patterns
The TokeniserPatternManager will read patterns from a list of strings, typically stored in a file.

The list of strings should contain default decisions for the various separators, in lines as follows:
IS_NOT_SEPARATOR -
IS_SEPARATOR_AFTER '
IS_SEPARATOR_BEFORE
All other separators are assumed to separate tokens on both sides (IS_SEPARATOR)

Next, it should contain a list of patterns.
Optionally, each pattern can be preceded by a user-friendly name and a tab.
Patterns are used to check if any set of n atomic tokens in a sentence matches it.

TokenPattern - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.patterns
A pattern for analysing whether a particular token is likely to have a TokeniserDecision different from the default for this token.
When matching a TokeniserPattern, we check if any set of n tokens in a TokenSequence matches it.
If so, all of the tokens inside the set are to be tested further, unless they have been marked with {} as not for further testing.
The TokeniserPattern will always match an exact number of tokens in a TokenSequence.
The number of tokens n to be matched is calculated from the number of separators explicitly included in the TokeniserPattern.
For example, the pattern "parce que" and "parce qu'" need to be listed separately, as the second one has an additional separator.
TokenPatternMatch - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.patterns
A single match for a token on a given TokeniserPattern, giving the index of the match.
TokenPatternMatchFeature<Y> - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.features
A feature which tests a TokenPatternMatch during tokenising.
TokenPatternMatchSequence - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.patterns
A token sub-sequence matching a particular TokenPattern within a larger token sequence (representing a sentence).
TokenPlaceholder - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.filters
A place-holder that will be replaced by a proper token when tokenising.
TokenRegexBasedCorpusReader - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser
A corpus reader that expects one token per line, and analyses the line content based on a regex.
The regex needs to contain a capturing group indicated by the following strings:
%TOKEN%: the token - note that we assume CoNLL formatting (with underscores for spaces and for empty tokens).
TokenRegexFilter - Interface in com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.filters
A token filter which recognises a token based on a regular expression.
TokenSearchFeature - Class in com.joliciel.talismane.parser.features
Returns the first token in a given range which matches a certain criterion, or null if no such token is found.
If a start index is provided as a second argument, will start looking at this index.
If an end index is provided as a third argument, will continue until the end index.
All indexes must be <= the current history size, otherwise only valid indexes will be looked at.
If start index >= end index, will look backwards, otherwise will look forwards.
A stopCriterion can be provided, in which case the search will stop as soon as the stop criterion is hit.
